# Autonomous Research Agent — Bootcamp Roadmap

## What We're Building

A production-quality multi-agent AI system where:
1. **Planner** breaks a research goal into 3–5 sub-questions
2. **Searcher** uses Tavily to search the web for each sub-question
3. **Writer** synthesizes all results into a structured report with citations
4. **Critic** scores the report. If < 7 → retry loop. If ≥ 7 → finalize.
5. **Frontend** shows each agent's reasoning steps live in a sidebar
6. **Supabase** saves all sessions. Users log in and see past research.

---

## Architecture Diagram

```
User (Next.js) ──POST /research──► FastAPI
                                      │
                              LangGraph Runner
                             ┌────────┴────────┐
                          Planner           AgentState
                             │         (shared memory)
                          Searcher
                        (Tavily API)
                             │
                          Writer
                        (OpenAI GPT)
                             │
                          Critic ──score < 7──► Searcher (retry)
                             │
                          score ≥ 7
                             │
                      Save to Supabase
                             │
                      WebSocket stream ──► Frontend sidebar (live steps)
```

---

## Tech Stack & Why Each Tool

| Tool | Role | Why |
|---|---|---|
| **LangGraph** | Agent orchestration | Stateful graph — nodes, edges, conditional routing, retry loops |
| **OpenAI gpt-4o-mini** | Planner, Writer, Critic | Cheapest capable model. Enough for structured outputs |
| **Tavily API** | Web search | Built for LLM agents. Returns clean markdown results |
| **FastAPI** | Backend API | Async Python, WebSocket support, auto Swagger docs |
| **Next.js + shadcn/ui** | Frontend | Production-grade React + professional pre-built components |
| **Supabase** | Database + Auth | Free Postgres + auth with 1 min setup. No backend auth code needed |
| **Railway** | FastAPI hosting | Git-push deploy, free tier, auto env management |
| **Vercel** | Next.js hosting | Instant deploy from GitHub, best-in-class for Next.js |

