## Phase Breakdown

### Phase 0 — Foundation Setup
**You'll learn:** Python project structure, virtual environments, API key management, testing third-party APIs

**What gets built:**
- Project folder created
- Python venv + all dependencies installed
- `.env` file with OpenAI, Tavily, Supabase keys
- Two test scripts: one calls OpenAI, one calls Tavily — just to confirm keys work

---

### Phase 1 — LangGraph Agents (The Core)
**You'll learn:** LangGraph state machines, how to build nodes/edges, conditional routing, retry logic

**What gets built:**
- `AgentState` — the shared memory object passed between all agents
- `Planner` node — calls GPT, returns list of sub-questions
- `Searcher` node — calls Tavily for each sub-question, stores results
- `Writer` node — calls GPT, returns structured report with citations
- `Critic` node — calls GPT, returns score + feedback
- `research_graph.py` — wires everything together with retry edge
- **End-to-end test in terminal**: type a goal, see the full agent loop run

---

### Phase 2 — FastAPI Backend
**You'll learn:** REST API design, async Python, WebSockets for real-time streaming

**What gets built:**
- `POST /research` — starts a new research run
- `GET /ws/{session_id}` — WebSocket that streams each agent step live
- `GET /sessions` — returns all past sessions for a user
- CORS setup for Next.js

---

### Phase 3 — Supabase Integration
**You'll learn:** SQL schema design, Supabase Python client, auth token flow

**What gets built:**
- `research_sessions` table in Supabase
- Save completed session (goal, sub-questions, report, score, timestamp)
- Fetch sessions by user
- Row-level security so users only see their own sessions

---

### Phase 4 — Next.js Frontend
**You'll learn:** Next.js app router, shadcn/ui components, WebSocket in React, Supabase Auth

**What gets built:**
- Research input page with goal form
- Live agent sidebar (WebSocket-powered, shows each step as it happens)
- Final report view with citations
- Session history page
- Login/Signup with Supabase Auth

---

### Phase 5 — Deployment
**You'll learn:** Environment variables in production, Railway + Vercel deploy, debugging prod builds

**What gets built:**
- FastAPI live on Railway URL
- Next.js live on Vercel URL
- Working end-to-end in production

---

